symbol.title: Ignore entire layer when generating stitch plan

use.inkscape:label: Ink/Stitch Command: Ignore layer (do not stitch any objects in this layer)

text.tspan: These objects may not work properly with Ink/Stitch. Follow
the instructions to correct unwanted behaviour.
Ink/Stitch can't work with objects like images.
* Convert your image into a path: Path > Trace Bitmap...
* Alternatively redraw the image with the pen (P) or bezier
It is possible, that one object contains more than one
error, yet there will be only one pointer per object. Run
this function again, when further errors occur. Remove
pointers by deleting the layer named "Troubleshoot" through
